    <p>A year ago, the Asia-Pa­cific seemed des­tined for an avi­a­tion boom. Then, the coro­n­avirus struck. Ja­pan’s ANA has placed around 43,500 em­ploy­ees on fur­lough. In In­dia, air­lines have shed over 18,000 jobs. Pi­lots are tak­ing up odd jobs to make ends meet. In­sight takes stock.</p>

